powerleveling up 3 or more of the accounts at once for sale and then repeating the process. <br>  <br> How do I feel about it? Well, for some folks their time is alot more valuable then their money, they have extremely limited free time to devote to a game and just want to dive right into high end game in EQ. They do not have the time nor interest in completing quests or earning drops on their own which are largely just timesinks or in many cases just find the sub level 55 game extremely tedious. I honestly wouldn't care at all so long as one of these folks never expects me to carry them along for weeks or months teaching them the basics of the gameplay and knowledge such as where things are in a starting area zone. If these folks wanted to get their money's worth they should have insisted on a in-game tutorial from the guy they are buying from if they are new to the game.  <br>  <br> Honestly, nobody wants to listen to some moron bragging about how great his gear is and yet they have no idea where any of it came from or what half of it actually does. They certainly don't want this guy/girl behaving in a way that can only be described as &quot;newbish&quot; and endangering everyone around them in a 50+ zone where you expect people to know their role. <br>  <br> A week ago in PoV we had a warrior join the group who immediately says he can deal more damage then anyone else because he has max dexterity so he hardly ever misses when he swings. I ask and figure out he had been killing things in a newbie zone for days. The first thing he does is run off and attack someone else's pulls they are running back to their group midway, attracting more mobs attention to himself and the cleric is /gsaying &quot;Should I heal him or not?&quot; <br> <p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr align="right" valign="bottom"><td colspan=2 class="BoardRowB"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/help/default.asp?goto=faqs%2Easp%23lockedtopic">Locked Topic</a> | <a href="/active_topic_notify.asp?mes=4672